Summary of Main Changes
• Refined the Taxonomy Structure: The original draft likely mixed "Graph RAG" (static retrieval) with "Agentic RAG" (dynamic reasoning). I have restructured the taxonomy to explicitly distinguish between Agentic workflows operating on Graphs (Navigation) and Agents constructing Graphs (Dynamic Knowledge).
• Clarified the "Agentic" Dimension: Moved general RAG definitions to the background and focused the core analysis on autonomy: how agents plan, decompose, and reflect using graph structures.
• Unified "Methods" Section: Grouped scattered methods into a cohesive "Architecture & Workflows" section, categorized by the role of the agent (e.g., Construction vs. Retrieval vs. Reasoning).
• Expanded Evaluation: Added specific subsections for evaluating the agentic aspect (e.g., reasoning path validity, tool-use accuracy) separate from standard retrieval metrics.
