4. Taxonomies of GA-RAG Systems
    4.1. By Integration Paradigm
        4.1.1. Graph-Augmented Agents — Agents use static graphs as a fixed tool for lookups to ground their reasoning.
        4.1.2. Graph-Centric Agents — The agent "lives" on the graph, navigating node-to-node (walking) to solve problems.
        4.1.3. Agent-Constructed Graphs — Agents actively build or modify the graph structure during the conversation to store memory.
    4.2. By Orchestration Architecture
        4.2.1. Single-Agent Frameworks — A single LLM orchestrator managing graph tools.
            4.2.1.1. ReAct on Graphs
            4.2.1.2. Chain-of-Thought (CoT) with Graph Paths
        4.2.2. Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) — Specialized agents (e.g., a "Retriever," a "Critic," a "Generator") collaborating over a shared graph.
            4.2.2.1. Hierarchical Teams (Manager-Worker)
            4.2.2.2. Cooperative / Debating Agents

